# Services

**Services = brain of the backend.**

- All business logic **must** live here (not routes, controllers, models, or middleware).
- Functions take plain arguments (IDs, DTOs) — **no `req` or `res`**.
- Return data or throw errors with `status` for the error middleware.
- Keep modules loosely coupled; shared logic in one service or `utils/`.

## Structure

```
services/
  authService.js
  userService.js
  chatService.js
  messageService.js
```

## Example

```javascript
// services/authService.js
const User = require("../models/User");
const generateToken = require("../utils/generateToken");

exports.register = async ({ name, email, password, age }) => {
  const existing = await User.findOne({ email });
  if (existing) {
    const err = new Error("User already exists");
    err.status = 400;
    throw err;
  }
  const user = await User.create({ name, email, password, age });
  return { user: formatUser(user), token: generateToken(user._id) };
};
```

New features: add or extend a service first, then wire a thin controller.
